data.description: Sellers are moving due to the need for more land to accommodate their puppies that were recently born.   Harford County holds the perfect balance of suburban and country life.  You’re in the country but close to shopping and all the amenities that make life convenient.  Major highways are a short distance away. This meticulously kept contemporary split foyer home located in the Rolling Green community is the perfect combination of country and suburban charm.  Just enough lawn space for great outdoor entertainment without a lot of outdoor maintenance nestled on 0.69 acres.  The roof, water filtration system, fencing, and interior are all very recently updated.  Entering through the beautiful front door you will find three bedrooms and two full baths on the upper level and one more bedroom, two spare bedrooms,  plus a den and full bath on the lower level. The spacious den shows off a beautiful fireplace with two sliding glass doors exiting to the backyard.  The den is spacious and great for entertainment.  All the bedrooms are roomy with adequate closet space.  Each bedroom is a short distance from the restroom.  Added storage space in the attic with the drop-down ladder.   The upper level has a spacious living room and dining room combination, a gourmet kitchen with lots of cabinet space all decorated in a white color theme.  The updated kitchen has been configured to include an open-concept idea that includes an island with quartz countertops and stainless-steel appliances. There is lots of cabinet space, expansive quartz counters, an awesome backsplash, a gas stove, a microwave, a dishwasher, a garbage disposal, and a refrigerator.   Beautiful new flooring throughout the entire home.   The utility room exits to the backyard for convenience.  The new water filter system is in the utility room along with the water heater and HVAC unit.   Privacy surrounds this home with a newly installed privacy fence. Plenty of parking space for multiple cars.  There is plenty of outside lighting surrounding the home both on the front sides and back!  Convenient car washing station in the parking area.  Short walk to the neighborhood park which includes great community amenities with access to the pier and beach on the lake.  Events occur during the year.   The Rolling Green Community Association is optional with no mandatory fees.  It is set up as a Community Organization (CoA), not a Homeowner’s Association (HOA).  It is totally voluntary to join, and those fees go toward the maintenance of the community.   The sellers are offering at no cost any items viewed in the photos to be sold free of charge with the home.  Home Warranty included on full price offer.
